#: ../../../../../CMake/wasm/README.md:2
msgid "VTK WASM regression test suite architecture"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/wasm/README.md:4
msgid ""
"The VTK Emscripten test utilities utilize a custom protocol designed to "
"address the file I/O requirements of WebAssembly (WASM) unit tests. This "
"protocol allows C++ unit tests to dump files from the sandbox to the server "
"hosting the WASM module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/wasm/README.md:6
msgid "Fixtures"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/wasm/README.md:8
msgid ""
"The test suite requires a HTTP server to run in the background. "
"Additionally, the tests expect to find a \"vtkhttp.lock\" file in the "
"`${CMAKE_BINARY_DIR}/Testing/Temporary` directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/wasm/README.md:10
msgid ""
"This lock file must contain the URL of a HTTP server that the tests may "
"connect to using web browser APIs. Right now, the connection is only made "
"when a unit test needs to dump a file (like difference images) to server "
"filesystem."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/wasm/README.md:13
msgid ""
"A new fixture called \"HTTP\" is used to coordinate the startup and shutdown "
"of the HTTP server. The special unit test `HTTPServerStart` is run before "
"all the unit tests that have \"HTTP\" in their `FIXTURES_REQUIRED` property "
"and finally the `HTTPServerStop` is run at the end to shutdown the HTTP "
"server."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/wasm/README.md:17
msgid "Arguments"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/wasm/README.md:19
msgid ""
"The command line for a unit test is set by the CMake functions in "
"vtkModuleTesting.cmake file. It looks like \"cmake\" -D... \"CMake/"
"vtkWasmTestRunner.cmake\" \"/path/to/vtkModuleNameCxxTests.js_file\" "
"\"TestName\" \"arg1\" \"arg2\" ... \"argn\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/wasm/README.md:22
msgid "Routes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/wasm/README.md:24
msgid "`/dump?file=/path/to/file.ext`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/wasm/README.md:26
msgid ""
"**Request description**: wasm unit test initiates a POST with the full path "
"of a file in its query parameters and sends the entire contents of the "
"output file in the POST content."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/wasm/README.md:28
msgid ""
"**Expected response**: No response needed if parameters are valid. 'Invalid "
"query for /dump' if query parameters are invalid."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/wasm/README.md:30
msgid "`/preload?file=[Drive:]/path/to/host_file.ext`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/wasm/README.md:32
msgid ""
"**Request description**: wasm unit test initiates a GET with the full path "
"of a file on the host filesystem in its query parameters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/wasm/README.md:34
msgid ""
"**Expected response**: The entire contents of the requested file if it "
"exists. 'File not found' if the file does not exist."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/wasm/README.md:36
msgid "`/favicon.ico`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/wasm/README.md:38
msgid "**Request description**: Browser requests the favicon for the server."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/wasm/README.md:40
msgid "**Expected response**: An empty response with 200 OK status is fine."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/wasm/README.md:42
msgid "`/VTK<ModuleName>/test.html`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/wasm/README.md:44
msgid ""
"**Request description**: Browser requests the test HTML page for a given VTK "
"module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/wasm/README.md:46
msgid ""
"**Expected response**: The HTML page that loads the corresponding wasm "
"module and runs the tests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/wasm/README.md:48
msgid "`/VTK<ModuleName>/vtk<ModuleName>CxxTests.js`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/wasm/README.md:50
msgid ""
"**Request description**: Browser requests the wasm JS file for a given VTK "
"module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/wasm/README.md:52
msgid ""
"**Expected response**: The wasm JS file that contains the compiled "
"WebAssembly module and its JavaScript glue code. This file is located in the "
"CMake build directory under `${CMAKE_RUNTIME_OUTPUT_DIRECTORY}`."
msgstr ""

